become real nature, in&s;tead of imitative.'</Q></P>
<P>Charles laughed heartily at this de&s;cription, and then
re&s;uming a more &s;erious air, a&s;ked if there were any in&s;tances of
the&s;e &s;ort of amours.</P>
<P> 
<Q REND="inline">'Indeed there are,' an&s;wered the other.
'Gen|teel young fellows never need be without them, and it is their own faults
